WEBVTT

00:01.826 --> 00:07.474
If an enemy is attacking you, you tend to know it.

00:10.518 --> 00:16.967
If an enemy is tempting you, you often are aware of that.

00:19.410 --> 00:28.983
If an enemy is accusing you, you usually know that's happening.

00:30.925 --> 00:31.346
But,

00:33.218 --> 00:43.031
If an enemy is deceiving you, you absolutely have no idea that it's happening.

00:45.675 --> 00:54.546
We've been talking the last few weeks from the end of 1 John that the whole world is under the control of the evil one.

00:56.129 --> 01:03.218
But of all of the things that the evil one does, attack, tempt,

01:04.162 --> 01:10.849
accuse the worst thing that he does is deceive.

01:12.150 --> 01:16.074
Jesus calls Satan the father of lies.

01:17.255 --> 01:20.258
He was a liar from the beginning.

01:21.279 --> 01:28.146
And when he speaks, he speaks his native language, which is lies.

01:29.667 --> 01:32.530
He deceives all the time.

01:33.986 --> 01:54.228
And while attacks are terrible and temptations are terrible and accusations are terrible, there is nothing as terrible as deception because a deceived person does not know they are being deceived.

01:57.112 --> 02:02.898
Currently in our country in America and in countries around the world,

02:03.874 --> 02:08.139
The political and cultural right is in ascendancy.

02:09.861 --> 02:27.984
General ideas that often go with the political and cultural right, the idea of personal individual freedom, market-driven economies, the use of force in keeping the rule of law, these kinds of things, these ideas tend to be more to the forefront.

02:28.064 --> 02:32.850
And many of us resonate with these aspects of the political

02:32.994 --> 02:34.216
and cultural right.

02:36.459 --> 02:44.691
But just a few years ago, the political and cultural left in America was more dominant force.

02:44.711 --> 03:00.114
The idea of environmentalism or diversity and inclusion, the idea of freedom from social norms, those sorts of things that are associated with the political and cultural left, those were the dominant ideas of the day, and many of us

03:00.194 --> 03:04.579
find ourselves resonating with the political and cultural left.

03:08.244 --> 03:29.330
But the truth is, if the whole world is under the control of the evil one, then there is absolutely deception on both the political and cultural right and on the political and cultural left.

03:29.954 --> 03:40.530
And the problem with deception is most of us can only see the deception on the side that we don't resonate with.

03:45.237 --> 03:52.268
But it's not half the world that's under the control of the evil one.

03:52.288 --> 03:59.058
It's not just half the technologies, half of the systems, half of the governments,

03:59.266 --> 04:01.288
that are under the control of the evil one.

04:02.369 --> 04:05.713
It's not like Satan's in control of Hollywood, but not Wall Street.

04:07.495 --> 04:12.180
Or Satan's in control of Silicon Valley, but not Washington DC.

04:12.200 --> 04:22.712
The whole world is under the control of the evil one, which means there is deception everywhere.

04:24.414 --> 04:28.018
Not just on the side we don't resonate with,

04:28.322 --> 04:30.785
But on our side as well.

04:34.429 --> 04:36.611
But if there is deception everywhere.

04:38.733 --> 04:46.141
And the problem with deception is the person being deceived doesn't know they're being deceived.

04:48.244 --> 04:49.265
What hope is there?

04:50.806 --> 04:57.714
How could anyone ever identify truth in the midst

04:57.858 --> 05:01.624
of a world that is being deceived.

05:03.506 --> 05:19.430
Well, at the end of the letter of 1 John as we studied a couple weeks ago, after God announces the bad news that the whole world is being deceived by Satan, he also announces the good news.

05:20.492 --> 05:27.282
The church is not under Satan's control and that God has provided

05:28.386 --> 05:39.959
through Jesus, a way that you and I can be undisceived in a world that is full of deception.

05:41.601 --> 05:43.664
We want to think together about that today.

05:44.465 --> 05:49.791
So let me invite you to take a Bible and turn to the letter of 2 John.

05:49.811 --> 05:53.455
2 John is right near the end of the Bible.

05:53.515 --> 05:55.858
It's page 989.

05:57.058 --> 05:59.081
in the Bibles in the rack in front of you.

06:06.851 --> 06:07.792
Second, John.

06:10.015 --> 06:13.400
It's the perfect follow-up to the end of first, John.

06:14.561 --> 06:26.898
The end of first, John, God says, the whole world's under Satan's control, but through Jesus, God has made a way for us to know the truth.

06:28.290 --> 06:30.332
Second John follows up on that.

06:32.374 --> 06:37.939
We're gonna read verses seven to 13, the second half of Second John page 989.

06:41.803 --> 06:54.175
John writes in verse seven, I say this because many deceivers who do not acknowledge Jesus Christ as coming in the flesh have gone out into the world.

06:55.797 --> 06:57.298
Any such person

06:57.890 --> 07:01.516
is the deceiver and the antichrist.

07:02.818 --> 07:09.449
Watch out that you do not lose what we have worked for, but that you may be rewarded fully.

07:10.651 --> 07:16.480
Anyone who runs ahead and does not continue in the teaching of Christ does not have God.

07:17.342 --> 07:22.230
Whoever continues in the teaching has both the Father and the Son.

07:23.311 --> 07:24.914
If anyone comes to you

07:25.346 --> 07:28.069
and does not bring this teaching.

07:29.090 --> 07:32.252
Do not take them into your house or welcome them.

07:33.233 --> 07:37.317
Anyone who welcomes them shares in their wicked work.

07:38.959 --> 07:42.702
I have much to write you, but I do not want to use paper and ink.

07:43.403 --> 07:49.148
Instead, I hope to visit you and talk with you face to face so that our joy may be complete.

07:50.089 --> 07:55.154
The children of your sister who is chosen by God send their greetings.

07:56.130 --> 08:03.220
Now I said last week, if you come back this week, you will get to see the completion of an entire book of the Bible.

08:04.221 --> 08:09.148
So here you are, last week the first half of second John, this week the second half of second John.

08:09.609 --> 08:10.290
And guess what?

08:10.350 --> 08:16.798
If you've been here for just two weeks, you can be like, I attended Calvary Church as they preached through an entire book of the Bible.

08:17.439 --> 08:18.961
So good for you, we're glad you're here.

08:20.904 --> 08:25.170
But we need to not forget that the second half of the book of John

08:26.242 --> 08:30.308
is intimately connected to the first half of the book of 2nd John.

08:32.911 --> 08:40.422
John starts our passage, verse 7, I say this because, well, what's the this?

08:41.343 --> 08:46.891
Well, it's what he just said at the end of last week's message in verse 6.

08:47.833 --> 08:51.698
In verse 6, what Jesus was telling us was that we as a church

08:53.186 --> 08:57.273
need to collectively show love to the world.

08:58.775 --> 08:59.216
Why?

09:00.237 --> 09:06.307
I say this because many deceivers have gone out into the world.

09:07.289 --> 09:18.527
The reason why God needs the church to love the world is because the whole world is being deceived.

09:18.547 --> 09:20.690
Not just one side or the other,

09:21.122 --> 09:25.988
Not just one set of technologies or one government or one culture or one system.

09:26.008 --> 09:29.873
The whole world is subject to deception.

09:31.795 --> 09:39.064
And God says, I need the church, us, collectively, to be love in this world.

09:41.707 --> 09:44.230
How do we do that?

09:44.250 --> 09:47.634
Well, the first half of Second John is about love.

09:49.122 --> 09:53.208
The second half of 2nd John is about truth.

09:55.251 --> 09:56.253
And it feels bare with me.

09:56.293 --> 09:58.396
The parallel works something like this.

09:59.938 --> 10:16.142
In verse five of 2nd John, God says, I need you, ah, set Calvary, to love each other internally so that we collectively, as Calvary Church, can love the world because of deception.

10:16.884 --> 10:18.546
So we love in here,

10:19.234 --> 10:20.737
so that we can love out there.

10:22.720 --> 10:26.086
The second half of second John works the same way.

10:26.847 --> 10:38.668
Verses eight to 11 say it is of utmost importance that there not be deception in here, so that we can bear truth out there.

10:39.890 --> 10:44.498
Verse seven says, the world needs truth in love.

10:45.698 --> 11:01.013
verses eight to 11 says, there's of utmost importance that we in here must know the truth so that we as a church can bear witness in a world that is lost in deception to that which is true.

11:02.975 --> 11:07.319
Which comes down to the all important question.

11:07.339 --> 11:09.941
Where do we find this truth?

11:10.101 --> 11:14.866
What is this truth that will save us

11:15.618 --> 11:18.482
from the deceptions of this world.

11:20.044 --> 11:34.425
It turns out the one truth that rescues us and this world from the deceptions of the evil one is found in verse 7.

11:37.410 --> 11:43.058
Jesus Christ coming in the flesh.

11:44.738 --> 12:12.402
the incarnation of Jesus is the truth that saves us from being deceived in this world and is the truth that will rescue this world from the deceptions, the antichrists, the plots and plans of the Father of life.

12:14.242 --> 12:23.494
It all boils down to Jesus Christ, God incarnate coming in the flesh.

12:25.696 --> 12:39.794
So this morning, let me give us five truths that we can draw from the incarnation that if we understand these, believe these, get these, live these, own these,

12:40.450 --> 12:53.510
They will rescue us from the deceptions of this world, whether on the political and cultural left, or the political cultural right, or somewhere in between.

12:54.873 --> 12:57.997
Five truths, all based in the incarnation.

13:00.181 --> 13:05.189
Number one, God loves us.

13:06.811 --> 13:08.594
God loves you.

13:09.506 --> 13:10.407
God loves me.

13:11.409 --> 13:12.911
God loves this world.

13:12.931 --> 13:16.357
1 John 5 verse 9.

13:17.078 --> 13:21.144
This is how God showed his love among us.

13:22.006 --> 13:28.075
He sent his one and only son into the world that we might live through him.

13:28.135 --> 13:33.684
The first truth that the incarnation teaches us is that we are loved by God.

13:35.527 --> 13:37.650
I've said this before and I will say it again.

13:38.562 --> 13:49.017
The most momentous truth in all the universe is that God is love.

13:49.037 --> 13:56.207
And God demonstrates his love for us in that Jesus became human.

13:56.227 --> 14:01.013
The incarnation is the objective statement of this truth.

14:01.354 --> 14:03.377
You are loved by God.

14:04.478 --> 14:07.282
This, by the way, is the root lie.

14:08.194 --> 14:24.754
that the Father of lies uses all the time, telling us that somehow God is angry with us, that God doesn't care about us, that God's busy with other things, that if God really loved us, He wouldn't let us go through what we're going through.

14:24.974 --> 14:37.970
If God really loved us, He would do something about the doubts that we have, or the physical suffering we have, or the mental anguish that we're going through, that if God really loved us, He wouldn't withhold these things that we want

14:38.082 --> 14:48.373
from us, this is the root lie, and the incarnation is trying to save us from this deception, which is you are loved.

14:48.393 --> 14:57.303
You are of no matter what you do, no matter who you are, you are loved.

14:57.323 --> 15:07.314
And many of the deceptions in this world would melt away if we could grasp and understand how loved we are.

15:08.034 --> 15:08.575
by God.

15:11.058 --> 15:13.981
Second truth that the incarnation teaches us.

15:15.603 --> 15:20.269
Selflessness is the pathway to blessing.

15:21.330 --> 15:23.953
I wanted this point to be longer, but it didn't look as good on the screen.

15:23.973 --> 15:37.810
What it really should be, selflessness, sacrifice, and suffering are the pathway to blessing in Philippians chapter two.

15:38.722 --> 15:57.143
We are told that even though Jesus is God, he did not consider his deity as something to be held onto, but instead, being self-less, he became a human, the incarnation.

15:58.445 --> 16:06.514
And not only did he become a human, he became obedient to the worst possible suffering

16:06.786 --> 16:12.315
even to the point of dying in rejection from his father.

16:13.556 --> 16:31.765
Because he did this, God has given Jesus the name that is above every name, that at the name of Jesus every knee will bow in heaven and on earth and under the earth and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord.

16:32.786 --> 16:35.250
Jesus himself said, the son of man, me,

16:35.458 --> 16:43.616
did not come to be served but to serve and to give his life as a ransom for many.

16:44.458 --> 16:49.810
The world tells us that selfishness is the pathway to blessing.

16:50.178 --> 17:05.576
The world tells us that if you and I seek after political power or money or education or influence or relationships or feeling good or money or whatever it may be, that this is the pathway to blessing.

17:07.698 --> 17:18.290
But if we can grasp the truth, that selflessness, suffering and sacrifice, this is actually the pathway to blessing.

17:19.874 --> 17:24.822
that will rescue us from many of the deceptions in this world.

17:27.486 --> 17:30.450
Truth number three, from the incarnation.

17:32.513 --> 17:35.999
Sin requires a payment.

17:38.002 --> 17:48.818
In Galatians 2, verse 21, it says this, I do not set aside the grace of God, for if righteousness could be gained through the law

17:49.698 --> 17:52.902
Christ died for nothing.

17:53.823 --> 18:00.490
What Paul is trying to say in Galatians is, look, if sin's not a big deal, why did Jesus become human?

18:01.531 --> 18:11.323
If it doesn't really matter, if God could have just waved His hand and said, oh, that's okay, why would He have His Son become human for eternity?

18:12.844 --> 18:14.386
Why would He have Him do this?

18:15.714 --> 18:19.478
The deceptions in this world are either, oh no, sin's not that big a deal.

18:19.498 --> 18:20.879
You just don't have to worry about it.

18:21.440 --> 18:25.124
Or no, no, we can handle sin through law and behavior.

18:26.205 --> 18:32.592
Both of those things underestimate the power of sin and Satan's deceiving us on both sides.

18:33.973 --> 18:42.322
The truth of the matter is if sin was easily dealt with, God would have chosen any other way.

18:43.842 --> 18:50.491
But the truth of the incarnation is sin is absolutely eternally serious.

18:53.555 --> 19:02.847
And Jesus became human because there was no other way, no other way.

19:02.868 --> 19:10.017
The more we grasp that truth, the more it will save us from the deceptions that are all over this world.

19:12.981 --> 19:13.682
Number four,

19:15.970 --> 19:19.395
All humans have dignity.

19:22.619 --> 19:37.300
James chapter three, God says this, with the tongue we praise our Lord and Father, and with it we curse human beings who have been made in God's likeness.

19:38.742 --> 19:44.690
Out of the same mouth, come praise and cursing my brothers and sisters, this

19:44.866 --> 19:46.889
should not be.

19:48.551 --> 20:08.518
James is saying that all human beings, regardless of sexual orientation, regardless of sinfulness, ability or disability, age, gender, all human beings, all human beings are created in the image of God.

20:09.279 --> 20:11.442
That gives every human being dignity.

20:12.482 --> 20:19.731
But how much more dignity do humans have because God is now one of us?

20:21.714 --> 20:24.457
Jesus has become human.

20:25.879 --> 20:31.687
This dignifies humanity in an infinite way.

20:32.407 --> 20:40.658
This is why Jesus says in Matthew 25, look, the stuff you did for the prisoner, the stuff you did for the foreigner,

20:41.378 --> 20:43.561
The stuff you did for the fatherless person.

20:44.503 --> 20:46.566
The stuff you did for the poor person.

20:47.508 --> 20:49.791
The stuff you did for the lonely person.

20:50.272 --> 20:52.235
You were doing that for me.

20:52.495 --> 20:52.836
Why?

20:52.936 --> 20:55.480
Because as a human, Jesus is our brother.

20:55.520 --> 21:02.170
And any kindness and dignity you and I show to another human being.

21:04.053 --> 21:05.015
We're showing to Jesus.

21:07.138 --> 21:09.682
Because Jesus is human.

21:10.082 --> 21:13.366
The incarnation changes everything.

21:17.091 --> 21:21.237
No other human deserves the same level of honor and praise that Jesus does.

21:22.959 --> 21:34.114
But every single human deserves dignity, care, and compassion because Jesus is human.

21:37.118 --> 21:39.762
Truth number five from the incarnation.

21:40.994 --> 21:43.156
truth is a person.

21:45.058 --> 21:46.440
And we have to follow his example.

21:47.962 --> 21:49.043
Truth is a person.

21:51.606 --> 21:56.811
In this world, we are told that truth is abstract ideas.

21:58.553 --> 22:00.956
But Jesus says, I am the truth.

22:03.499 --> 22:06.482
Truth is a living person.

22:06.978 --> 22:12.305
and truth became a person so that we might follow his example.

22:12.325 --> 22:24.720
1 Peter 2, verse 21 to 23 says, to this you were called because Christ suffered for you, leaving you what?

22:25.801 --> 22:30.367
An example that you and I should follow in his steps.

22:30.848 --> 22:32.690
He committed no sin

22:33.122 --> 22:35.164
and no deceit was found in his mouth.

22:35.405 --> 22:40.270
When they hurled insults at him, he did not retaliate.

22:41.251 --> 22:43.834
When he suffered, he made no threats.

22:45.156 --> 22:51.924
Instead, he entrusted himself to the one who judges, justly.

22:55.148 --> 22:56.769
Truth is not a set of ideas.

22:58.491 --> 23:00.754
Truth is an incarnate person.

23:02.050 --> 23:16.872
And when we walk like Jesus, when we act like Jesus, when we talk like Jesus, when we interact with our enemies, the way that Jesus interacted with his enemies, when we endure suffering the way Jesus endured suffering, we are not being deceived.

23:18.134 --> 23:25.806
The more we grasp this truth, the less we are susceptible to the deceptions of this world.

23:28.149 --> 23:31.474
These are five truths that the incarnation teaches us.

23:32.802 --> 23:39.451
The more we understand these truths, the less power the Father of lies has over us.

23:44.218 --> 23:48.424
Now that's very hopefully beautiful and theological and a blessing.

23:49.405 --> 23:52.570
But let me give you a few practical things from this as well.

23:55.374 --> 23:58.258
Look with me at verse 12 of 2nd John.

24:01.826 --> 24:06.773
This is the doorway into some very practical applications of this incarnational truth.

24:07.454 --> 24:13.642
John says, I have much to write to you, but I do not want to use paper and ink.

24:15.645 --> 24:24.056
Instead, I hope to visit you and talk with you face to face so that our joy may be complete.

24:25.498 --> 24:27.581
Please do not miss what John is saying.

24:28.803 --> 24:31.186
John is writing scripture.

24:32.290 --> 24:32.730
You understand?

24:32.750 --> 24:36.034
He's writing the inspired Word of God.

24:36.795 --> 24:45.144
He's writing 2nd John and he says, I have more to say to you, but I'm not going to write it down.

24:45.764 --> 24:46.245
Why?

24:48.227 --> 24:58.418
Because something more happens in incarnational face-to-face ministry that can't even happen through the Scriptures.

25:00.642 --> 25:10.866
Second, John is not any longer because John realized there are things I need to do face to face.

25:12.710 --> 25:14.354
I mean, John himself says this in his gospel.

25:14.374 --> 25:19.506
He's like, look, if we tried to write down everything that Jesus did, there wouldn't be enough books.

25:22.338 --> 25:27.123
If all it was was just an instruction book, then why did Jesus become human?

25:27.423 --> 25:32.388
Why didn't God just drop the instruction manual from the sky and say, hey, read this and do that?

25:33.869 --> 25:39.354
It's because the incarnation cannot be replaced by anything else.

25:39.574 --> 25:42.197
There is something that happens face to face.

25:42.437 --> 25:44.859
There is something that happens incarnationally.

25:45.060 --> 25:51.826
There is something that happens through presence that not even the scripture itself can accomplish.

25:52.578 --> 25:58.464
This is why the Scriptures without the Spirit are useless.

26:01.347 --> 26:14.960
So practically speaking, this means if you've got something to say to another person, email and text is your last choice, especially if it's something difficult.

26:16.021 --> 26:21.266
A phone call is better than an email and an in-person meeting is better than a phone call.

26:22.498 --> 26:26.063
truth is meant to be communicated face to face.

26:26.123 --> 26:44.710
And if you have something hard to say to somebody, if you've got to point out to somebody, somebody has sin in their life, if you've got to tell them how they've hurt you, we're looking for face to face interactions as much as possible because there is something that is communicated human to human.

26:45.411 --> 26:50.418
That even the written word of God cannot communicate.

26:53.058 --> 26:58.144
Now I'm not devaluing the Bible because the Bible with the Spirit is infinitely powerful.

27:00.026 --> 27:08.976
But the truth of what John is writing here is trying to tell us, look, if this stuff could be accomplished from a distance, then Jesus would have remained in heaven.

27:10.117 --> 27:12.720
It has to be done face to face.

27:15.363 --> 27:21.330
This is why AI, social media, and dating apps,

27:22.050 --> 27:25.435
will always be subject to deception.

27:26.757 --> 27:36.771
It doesn't mean they can't be used for good, but they are especially susceptible to deception because they are not embodied experiences.

27:40.496 --> 27:43.300
The problem with deception is you don't know when you're being deceived.

27:45.003 --> 27:46.765
It's really helpful to recognize.

27:47.807 --> 27:50.290
AI is just giving you words.

27:51.362 --> 27:52.143
There's no life.

27:53.245 --> 27:54.166
There's no spirit.

27:54.987 --> 27:55.909
There's no body.

27:57.731 --> 28:06.504
Those words can be used by God for good, but they are especially subject to deception because of this.

28:06.765 --> 28:21.266
Listen, if John can't even put the words into inspired scripture without being face to face, what hope is there that a dating app or a social media platform or AI is going to be able to communicate

28:21.346 --> 28:23.528
truth without embodiment.

28:24.550 --> 28:27.833
Again, it doesn't mean that those things can't be used for good.

28:28.094 --> 28:32.018
There is no part of me standing up here saying have nothing to do with that stuff.

28:32.038 --> 28:38.085
I'm just saying, beware, they will always be subject to deception.

28:39.386 --> 28:39.967
I mean, come on.

28:40.527 --> 28:46.054
If you've used a dating app, there's a lot of deception going on, right?

28:48.857 --> 28:49.938
It just proves the point.

28:51.266 --> 28:59.255
John himself said 2,000 years ago, look, even though I'm writing scripture, there's something far more powerful that happens face to face.

29:02.799 --> 29:08.425
This is why attending church in person is so absolutely important.

29:16.714 --> 29:20.338
There are many that can be here in person who watch online and we're grateful for that.

29:21.954 --> 29:25.600
but the ideal situation is that you come in person.

29:27.824 --> 29:33.614
Because incarnation is the protection against deception.

29:35.577 --> 29:37.140
We learn truth together.

29:38.262 --> 29:40.266
We encourage one another together.

29:41.267 --> 29:45.294
Jesus is present with us when we gather together.

29:45.334 --> 29:47.538
This is the plan.

29:48.002 --> 29:57.212
We spend the world living in deception and we come and we meet with Jesus each and every week so that He can help us be set free from those deceptions.

30:00.056 --> 30:07.484
This is why for Lent, we are encouraging you to share Jesus with neighbors, co-workers, friends.

30:08.565 --> 30:13.010
You might think to yourself, but there's somebody else that could better answer their questions than me.

30:13.922 --> 30:17.628
Or maybe they're going to get better answers on the internet to their intellectual questions.

30:17.929 --> 30:20.794
Or somebody else is going to have something better to say than I will.

30:22.416 --> 30:24.640
But you're present in their life.

30:25.081 --> 30:27.385
Don't underestimate the power of that.

30:28.627 --> 30:30.249
You're present in their life.

30:30.510 --> 30:31.411
You know them.

30:31.712 --> 30:32.693
They know you.

30:33.154 --> 30:35.638
And yes, you may not have the perfect answer to everything.

30:35.658 --> 30:36.159
But guess what?

30:36.440 --> 30:37.842
You're the perfect answer.

30:38.562 --> 30:46.413
The fact that you're in their life, the fact that you're praying for them, the fact that you care about them, you are Jesus to them.

30:48.015 --> 30:50.298
So don't think I got somebody else would do a better job.

30:50.318 --> 30:53.563
Know you're in their life for this reason.

30:55.125 --> 31:00.292
Simply handing them a book, giving them something to read on the internet.

31:01.654 --> 31:07.602
That does not have the same power as you as their friend, their cousin,

31:08.354 --> 31:16.002
their co-worker, the kid in school sitting next to them, when you look at them and say, hey, you want to come to church with me?

31:17.784 --> 31:22.389
When you say to them, look, I don't have all the answers to your questions, but I love Jesus, and he loves you too.

31:23.230 --> 31:26.013
There is nothing more powerful than that.

31:27.035 --> 31:29.297
That's why we're doing Lent the way we're doing it this year.

31:32.721 --> 31:37.426
This is also why the church is the hope for this city.

31:38.498 --> 31:39.139
and this world.

31:41.863 --> 31:45.468
We are the body of Christ.

31:46.469 --> 31:47.190
Do you know what that means?

31:48.212 --> 31:53.239
We are the incarnation of Jesus in Grand Rapids, Michigan today.

31:54.601 --> 31:56.123
Now there's other incarnations of Jesus.

31:56.143 --> 31:56.784
Thank God for that.

31:56.824 --> 31:57.725
We're not the only ones.

32:00.269 --> 32:02.412
But we are the body of Christ.

32:02.832 --> 32:03.573
No businesses.

32:04.394 --> 32:05.216
No government is.

32:05.917 --> 32:06.898
No school is.

32:07.490 --> 32:09.792
This is not said about anybody else.

32:10.333 --> 32:20.323
We are the incarnation of Jesus in this world, a world that is under the control of the evil one who has no idea how they're being deceived.

32:20.343 --> 32:28.030
The only hope for such a world is not more education, not better laws, not better policies.

32:28.090 --> 32:32.715
All that stuff is fine, but the hope when you're deceived, you don't know you're being deceived.

32:33.636 --> 32:36.018
To deceive people, all the laws look good.

32:36.546 --> 32:39.509
To deceive people, the educational stuff all sounds right.

32:40.570 --> 32:48.199
The only hope for deceived people is Jesus Christ in the flesh.

32:50.682 --> 32:56.228
When he left heaven, when he left to go to heaven, he did not leave this world alone.

32:57.329 --> 33:01.574
He said, I will send you my spirit and more two or three of you gather together in my name.

33:02.274 --> 33:05.458
I will be present and on this earth today,

33:06.658 --> 33:10.522
Jesus is incarnated in us.

33:15.488 --> 33:18.491
Government is an institution.

33:18.511 --> 33:20.133
Businesses are institutions.

33:21.214 --> 33:24.617
Schools are institutions.

33:24.637 --> 33:26.620
The church is a people.

33:28.201 --> 33:30.183
If we stop meeting, there wouldn't be a church.

33:31.265 --> 33:33.907
Some bylaws, not constitutions, it's not buildings.

33:34.408 --> 33:36.370
It is an embodied group

33:36.482 --> 33:46.546
of people, because we are the incarnation of Jesus in this world, and that's the only hope to avoid deception.

